<h3>Preparation</h3>

To check for proper installation at your site, run

<pre>
    $ ocs info
->  You are using `@ocs_version@'
->  located at `/usr/ocs'.
->  The project ($OCSPROJECT) is not specified.
</pre>

You should see output marked by <code>-></code> as above. (The
installation directory <code>/usr/ocs</code> may differ at your site).

<small><blockquote> If the command <code>ocs</code> is not found, you
must extend your search path by <code>/usr/ocs/bin</code>. (You might
also want to extend your manual path by <code>/usr/ocs/man</code>.) If
<code>"ocs info"</code> still doesn't work, check the installation at
your site <a href="http://uebb.cs.tu-berlin.de/~opal/opal-system.html">(see
	  installation guides)</a>.</blockquote> </small>

To run the examples discussed in this tutorial, you should copy the
directory <code>/usr/ocs/examples</code>:

<pre>
  $ cp -r /usr/ocs/examples .
</pre>

